Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2

Thank you for working on this!!!

Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

Thanks Cyril,

This looks in general good, just one thing I think we need to sort before this.

What do we do about any images lingering around that has still sheepdog locations in them?

Patch Set 1:

We should make sure we add a release note the very clearly calls this out in the upgrade section. I think with the state of the sheepdog project, there hopefully isn't anyone still running it. But if we can't programatically do something to safeguard against something still being present, we should make sure it's very clearly documented that something needs to be done before upgrading to this version of the code.

Patch Set 1:

@Erno: isn't that already an issue with sheepdog being removed from glance_store? What happens if an existing deployment uses sheepdog?

Patch Set 1: -Code-Review

Yes, but we have removed it from glance_store library this cycle, which is (IMO) still not used in any deployments. We need to take care of this as suggested by erno.

Patch Set 1:

I think Sean is right. We just need very strong message in the release notes that if someone was still using sheepdog those images will be in very bad state after upgrade.

Patch Set 1:

We discussed this at today's glance meeting.  This needs a release note and an upgrade check.

Patch Set 1:

Cyril, could you please do the needful?

Patch Set 1:

po files really shouldn't be modified. Those should be left to the translation update process.
